We are using a modified kitbot, and our coral and algae rollers are not working, we have the one coral roller motor (NEO V1.1 w/ a spark max) and 2 algae roller motors (same setup but twice). everything is set up using CAN and all of the robot movement motors (4x CIM’s on Spark MAX’s) work well with a logitech f310 gamepad. I am away from my programming laptop but code is soon to come, in the mean time are there any fixes anyone would like to suggest?

We’d definitely need some more info to determine the exact issue but here’s a few i guess.

  1. Make sure your SparkMAXes are configured for brushless motors (CIMs are brushed while NEOs are brushless)
  2. Make sure your CAN IDs are correct in code
  3. Double check that your code is actually telling the motor to move.
  4. Make sure your spark maxes are receiving power and blinking the correct LED code
